Mix salsas, cranberry sauce, sugar, mustard and nutmeg in large saucepot. Heat to a boil. Cook over low heat 10 min. Add pork and heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hr. or until pork is tender. Remove pork from sauce and cool slightly. Shred pork, using two forks. Return pork to sauce and heat through. Serve about 1/2 cup shredded pork in each roll. Top with lettuce and coleslaw.